BLUETONGUE - TURKEY: (ADANA) OVINE, SEROTYPES 8 & 4, OIE
********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 3 Jul 2017
Source: OIE, WAHID [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=28691


Information received [and dated] on 20 Nov 2018 from Dr Nihat Pakdil, Deputy Undersecretary of Ministry, Veterinary Services, Ministry of Food, Agriculture and Livestock, Ankara, Turkey

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 17 Sep 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 19 Nov 2018
Report date: 20 Nov 2018
Date submitted to OIE: 20 Nov 2018
Reason for notification: New strain of a listed disease in the country
Causal agent: Bluetongue virus
Serotype: 8
Nature of diagnosis: Clinical, Laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Isikli, Kozan, Adana
Date of start of the outbreak: 17 Sep 2018
Outbreak status Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Sheep / 214 / 23 / 11 / 0 / 0

Affected population: 1st symptoms of the disease were seen on 17 Sep 2018. The disease was detected as positive by Adana Veterinary Control Institute, which is the regional laboratory. Afterwards, defibrinated blood samples were sent for serotyping to Etlik Veterinary Control Central Research Institute, which is the national reference laboratory for bluetongue. As a result of the serotyping, 4 samples were detected as BTV8 positive; 15 samples were detected as BTV4 positive, and 4 samples were detected as both type positive.

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Sheep / 214 / 23 / 11 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed in percentages]
Species / Apparent morbidity rate / Apparent mortality rate / Apparent case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Sheep / 10.75 / 5.14 / 47.83 / 5.14
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Vectors

Epidemiological comments: Two different serotypes of the disease present at the same outbreak.

Control measures
Measures applied: Movement control inside the country, Surveillance within containment and/or protection zone, Quarantine, Disinfection, Control of vectors;
No treatment of affected animals.

Vaccination in response to the outbreak(s):
Administrative division / Species / Total Vaccinated
Adana / Sheep / 5800

Measures to be applied: No other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Etlik Veterinary Control Central Research Institute (National laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Sheep / real-time reverse transcriptase-polymerase chain reaction (RRT-PCR) / 19 Nov 2018 / Positive

Future Reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map at the source URL above.]

